                            jump to other results
                        </a></div></div><ol class="sense_single" htag="ol"><li class="sense" htag="li" hclass="sense" id="adams_sng_3"><span class="sensetop" htag="span" hclass="sensetop"><span class="def" hclass="def" htag="span">(1735-1826) the second President of the US after being the country's first <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/vice-president#vice_president_topg_1" title="vice-president definition"><span class="ndv">vice-president</span></a>. He was a leader in forming the <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/the-declaration-of-independence" title="Declaration of Independence definition"><span class="ndv">Declaration of Independence</span></a>. He was not a very popular president because of arguments within his government and problems in foreign relations, especially with France. He was the father of <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/john-quincy-adams" title="John Quincy Adams definition"><span class="ndv">John Quincy Adams</span></a>.</span></span>    <div id="ring-links-box">
